title: For Sale/Trade:  1943 Springfield M1 Garand
postcontent: For sale is an extremely well cared for Springfield M1 Garand, serial numbered as a product of September 1943. You won't find a better Christmas gift than this!WARTIME FIREARMS, LLC -- WE SHIP!!!The M1 Garand saw extensive service from WW2 and the Korean War, all the way up to the beginning of Vietnam, just before the M14 was introduced to service. Throughout the years, almost every M1 Garand was either scrapped for parts, or rebuilt to be put back into service. Very seldom will you touch an M1 Garand that wasn't held by a young man in an unfamiliar place, fighting for his life and his country. This Garand is no exception. It, too, went through the US Army's recycling program after WW2 and, judging by the date of the barrel, was likely used early on in Vietnam before it's retirement. The reciever is in immaculate condition, showing very little visible wear. The rifling in the 1962 Springfield Armory barrel is perfect, and it even boasts a Boyt rifle sling from the year 1942. The replacement stock fits snug and feels great in your hands.Overall, this is the M1 Garand to buy if you're a collector that occasionally likes to shoot his or her firearms.
